"has_issues":true,"has_projects":true,"has_downloads":true,"has_wiki":true,"has_pages":true,"has_discussions":true,"forks_count":754,"mirror_url":null,"archived":false,"disabled":false,"open_issues_count":248,"license":{"key":"apache-2.0","name":"Apache License 2.0","spdx_id":"Apache-2.0","url":"https://api.github.com/licenses/apache-2.0","node_id":"MDc6TGljZW5zZTI="},"allow_forking":true,"is_template":false,"web_commit_signoff_required":false,"topics":["assertions","assertj","groovy","hacktoberfest","java","kotlin","testing","typed-assertions"],"visibility":"public","forks":754,"open_issues":248,"watchers":2769,"default_branch":"main","permissions":{"admin":false,"maintain":false,"push":false,"triage":false,"pull":true}},"body":"#### Summary\r\nI'd like to be able to use more Assertion methods on the `ThrowableTypeAlternative` instance. Specifically, the methods defined in `AbstractObjectAssert`.\r\nIssue #663 addresses a similar thing; So I feel this class could also benefit from this change.\r\n\r\n#### Example\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/assertj/assertj-core/blob/30bfbbc257d1a5b59563323b5eea29099d73926f/src/main/java/org/assertj/core/api/ThrowableAssertAlternative.java#L29\r\n\r\nCould be:\r\n```java\r\npublic class ThrowableAssertAlternative<T extends Throwable> extends AbstractObjectAssert<ThrowableAssertAlternative<T>, T> {\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen, the following code:\r\n```java\r\n@Test\r\npublic void authenticateWithForbiddenResponse() {\r\n    when(response.getStatus()).thenReturn(SC_FORBIDDEN);\r\n    assertThatExceptionOfType(AuthenticationFailureException.class)\r\n        .isThrownBy(() -> authenticator.authenticate())\r\n        .satisfies(exception ->\r\n            assertThat(exception.getStatusCode())\r\n                .isEqualTo(SC_FORBIDDEN));\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\ncan turn into this:\r\n```java\r\n@Test\r\npublic void authenticateWithForbiddenResponse() {\r\n    when(response.getStatus()).thenReturn(SC_FORBIDDEN);\r\n    assertThatExceptionOfType(AuthenticationFailureException.class)\r\n        .isThrownBy(() -> authenticator.authenticate())\r\n        .returns(SC_FORBIDDEN, AuthenticationFailureException::getStatusCode);\r\n}\r\n```","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/assertj/assertj/issues/1461/reactions","total_count":2,"+1":2,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/assertj/assertj/issues/1461/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed"}},"event":"cross-referenced"}]